OL,6,F"Thankfully, the jury saw through his
OL,7,Flies and convicted him for this
OL,8,Fheinous crime against a defenceless
OL,9,Fwoman who had her whole life to look
OL,10,Fforward to ` and could never have
OL,11,Fimagined her own husband would cause
OL,12,Fher such serious harm.
OL,14,F"Jo's family have shown great dignity
OL,15,Fand strength through this difficult
OL,16,Fprocess, and our thoughts are with
OL,17,Fthem."
OL,19,FIn a statement, Mrs Samak's family
OL,20,Fdescribed her as an "amazing mummy".
